title: Infinite recursion instead of `cannot infer type`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust fn main() { sqlx::query("insert into ...") .bind(vec![]); } ``` `Cargo.toml`: ``` [dependencies] sqlx = { version = ">= 0.4.0-beta.1", default-features = false, features = [ "chrono", "runtime-tokio", "macros", "mysql", "postgres" ] } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.45.0 (5c1f21c3b 2020-07-13) binary: rustc commit-hash: 5c1f21c3b82297671ad3ae1e8c942d2ca92e84f2 commit-date: 2020-07-13 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.45.0 LLVM version: 10.0 ``` The bug happens in nightly, too: ``` rustc 1.46.0-nightly (67100f61e 2020-06-24) binary: rustc commit-hash: 67100f61e62a86f2bf9e38552ee138e231eddc74 commit-date: 2020-06-24 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.46.0-nightly LLVM version: 10.0 ``` ### Expected error `cannot infer type for vec![]`
Error output ``` Compiling sqlx_bug v0.1.0 (/home/daniela/Developer/sqlx_bug) error[E0275]: overflow evaluating the requirement `[(_, _, _, _, _, _, _, _)]: sqlx_core::types::Type` -->
